# TextInput — React

Package: `@acko/text-input`
Directive: `"use client"` (interactive)

## Props Interface

```typescript
interface TextInputProps {
  id?: string;
  label: string;
  placeholder?: string;
  value: string;
  onChange: (value: string) => void;
  size?: 'sm' | 'md' | 'lg';
  type?: 'text' | 'email' | 'password' | 'tel' | 'url' | 'search' | 'number';
  state?: 'default' | 'error' | 'success';
  helperText?: string;
  errorText?: string;
  disabled?: boolean;
  readOnly?: boolean;
  required?: boolean;
  iconLeft?: ReactNode;
  iconRight?: ReactNode;
  prefix?: string;
  suffix?: string;
  maxLength?: number;
  autoComplete?: string;
  className?: string;
}
```

## Key Behaviors

- Controlled component: `value` + `onChange`
- Internal `focused` state drives CSS class + label color
- Success state shows animated checkmark icon (inline SVG)
- Error text is wrapped in `role="alert"`

## Accessibility

- `aria-required`, `aria-invalid`, `aria-describedby`
- Label linked via `htmlFor` / `id`
- Error text with `role="alert"` for screen reader announcement

